        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 3:49PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fort Collins, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree branches and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Collins, northern Loveland, Windsor, Wellington, Timnath,
Laporte and New Windsor Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rain is occurring with this storm and may lead to street
flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
